  "description": "This open multimodal dataset combines intracranial EEG (iEEG) recordings and functional MRI data acquired simultaneously from patients with epilepsy during naturalistic audiovisual film stimulation. The dataset includes electrocorticographic recordings from implanted electrodes and whole-brain fMRI scans collected during passive viewing of a short film, providing a unique resource for studying neural responses to complex naturalistic stimuli across multiple spatial and temporal scales.",
  "methods_description": "Data were collected using simultaneous iEEG and fMRI acquisition during passive viewing of a short audiovisual film. Intracranial electrodes were implanted for clinical purposes in patients with epilepsy, and fMRI scans were acquired concurrently with electrocorticographic recordings.",
